    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2021" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέρας</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αος</span>, pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέρα</span>:
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">gift of honor, honor, prerogative;</span> nobles and esp.
          the king received <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέρα</span> from the
          commonalty, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γέρας θ᾽ ὅ τι δῆμος
          ἔδωκεν</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 7.150</span></i>; of the
          kingly office itself, <i><span class="en">Il. 20.182</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 11.175</span></i>; of offerings to the
          gods, and burial honors of the dead, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τὸ γὰρ
            γέρας ἐστὶ θανόντων</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
